message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. The paper presents a new reading comprehension dataset and builds a logistic regression model to answer questions on the dataset. This involves natural language processing, machine learning, and information retrieval, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of dependency and constituency trees suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
